}
```

It calls `self.invalidate_cached_bitmap()`. This is the trait method on `DisplayObject`:

```rust
fn invalidate_cached_bitmap(self) {
    if self.base().invalidate_cached_bitmap() {
        if let Some(parent) = self.parent() {
            parent.invalidate_cached_bitmap();
        }
    }
}
```

This walks up through parents. But note: `invalidate_cached_bitmap` returns `bool` - true if this is the first invalidation this frame. If it returns false (already invalidated), the chain STOPS at the Graphic.

So the question is: could the Graphic's `CACHE_INVALIDATED` flag already be set when `replace_with` is called?

During `Enter` phase:
